headline: New Study: Integrative Therapy and Nurse Navigation Reduce Treatment Side Effects for 75% of Black Breast Cancer Patients; 85% Report Lower Distress
summary: ANNAPOLIS, Md. & PHILADELPHIA, December 10, 2025--Leading breast cancer nonprofits Unite for HER and TOUCH, The Black Breast Cancer Alliance (TOUCHBBCA) presented new and critical research addressing health disparities, entitled "A New Comprehensive Integrative Care and Navigation Model for Enhancing Outcomes for Black Breast Cancer Patients: Evidence from the Care for HER Program​" at the 2025 San Antonio Breast Cancer Symposium.
